    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk, \"shining moment\" sounds like something people say to make themselves feel better so they don't lose it. it's just a coping mechanism. like, if you know a movie is a tragedy and it's gonna end in total destruction anyway, why even bother watching it? treating it like a \"shining moment\" is just lying to yourself about the reality of it all. it's all just noise before the silence.",
